# Whitelist approach: ignore everything at the repo root, then re-include
# the paths we care about. Blacklist rules at the bottom re-ignore generated
# and vendored content that would otherwise sneak in under whitelisted subtrees.

/*

# --- tracked top-level files -------------------------------------------------
!.gitignore
!.gitmodules
!/.github
!/CLAUDE.md
!/CONTRIBUTING.md
!/LICENSE
!/README.md

# --- tracked top-level directories -------------------------------------------
!/docs
!/host
!/models
!/script
!/src

# Recurse into the whitelisted directories (includes dotfiles under them).
!/.github/**
!/docs/**
!/host/**
!/models/**
!/script/**
!/src/**

# --- re-ignore generated / vendored content anywhere in the tree -------------

# Arduino / PlatformIO / CMake build outputs
**/build/
**/.pio/
**/.pioenvs/

# Python virtual environments and caches
**/venv/
**/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# KiCAD autosaves, caches, history and local state
*-backups/
**/fp-info-cache
**/.history/
*.kicad_prl

# KiCAD generated outputs (board plots & JLCPCB production files).
# Comment these out if you want to track fabrication artifacts.
**/plots/
**/jlcpcb/

# Editor / OS cruft
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
